==Competitive record==
All competitive matches played from 1921 to 1958 were contested as the [[Territory of Curaçao national football team|Territory of Curaçao]] (comprising all six islands of the Netherlands Antilles). From 1958 to 2010 all matches were contested as the [[Netherlands Antilles national football team|Netherlands Antilles]], successor of the Territory of Curaçao, (still comprising six islands until 1986, when Aruba seceded). All competitive fixtures after 2010 were contested by Curaçao, which solely consists of the island nation itself. Under the newly formed governing body, Curaçao have so far only competed in [[2014 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONCACAF)|2014]], [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONCACAF)|2018]] and [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONCACAF)|2022 FIFA World Cup qualification]], [[2012 Caribbean Cup qualification]], the [[2014 Caribbean Cup|2014]] and [[2017 Caribbean Cup]], the [[2017 CONCACAF Gold Cup]], [[2019 CONCACAF Gold Cup]], and the [[ABCS Tournament]].

